docs.lead_paragraph: PATERSON--Pharmacists have informed state officials that cutbacks in Medicaid payments scheduled for Friday could lead to reductions in prescription services.

headline.main: Druggists Concerned By Cutbacks In Medicaid

docs.abstract: NJ Pharmaceutical Assn informs NJ officials that 25c cut in Medicaid rebates scheduled for Aug 1 will lead to reductions in prescription services; urges public hearing; leaders of county orgns call meetings to determine actions druggists can take, including possible boycotting of Medicaid (M)
